WEBVTT

00:04.163 --> 00:07.414
Sean: Americans.

00:07.449 --> 00:11.118
When the day of judgment comes,
where do they seek refuge?

00:11.154 --> 00:12.715
A shopping mall.

00:13.115 --> 00:16.233
MacDowell reckons there
are 10,000 in the area.

00:16.258 --> 00:19.426
He says 5% of 'em may be immunes like us.

00:19.461 --> 00:24.013
15 million American immunes,
just waiting to join the cause.

00:24.049 --> 00:25.965
Net: Yeah, and how many of them

00:26.017 --> 00:28.468
are gonna go for your
"we are the chosen" act?

00:28.493 --> 00:30.442
It ain't no act.

00:32.140 --> 00:33.807
Ned.

00:33.859 --> 00:36.872
It ain't no act.

00:37.005 --> 00:38.672
Fine.

00:38.697 --> 00:42.172
Good, look, Sean, the labs are gone.

00:42.197 --> 00:44.711
The boys took care of the
ones in Lisbon and Istanbul.

00:44.736 --> 00:48.321
The only cure that's left
is sitting on that Navy ship.

00:48.323 --> 00:50.272
It's them we should be going after now.

00:50.297 --> 00:51.678
<i>Achilles</i> ain't no use to us

00:51.703 --> 00:53.003
until we repair the sound matting

00:53.028 --> 00:54.661
we scraped off in the canyons.

00:54.800 --> 00:57.101
Once we're good and quiet
again, Ian will get her moving

00:57.126 --> 00:59.293
and restart the hunt for the destroyer.

00:59.318 --> 01:02.385
And I say we join him
and the rest of our crew

01:02.410 --> 01:05.461
instead of mucking around
in this bloody swamp.

01:05.486 --> 01:06.819
Come on.

01:06.844 --> 01:08.594
Let's kill those Navy bastards

01:08.619 --> 01:10.737
and then bugger off back to England.

01:10.762 --> 01:12.997
Have you heard a bloody
word I've been saying?

01:13.022 --> 01:15.258
Ned, I have a plan.

01:15.283 --> 01:16.880
It's a shit plan.

01:16.905 --> 01:18.489
- Ned.
- Running from town to town,

01:18.514 --> 01:20.301
waiting for people to get the virus,

01:20.326 --> 01:22.028
and then picking through survivors

01:22.053 --> 01:23.731
looking for punters like us.

01:23.756 --> 01:25.506
- Ned.
- I hate this place.

01:26.626 --> 01:28.684
The heat.

01:29.509 --> 01:31.770
We should be home living the life.

01:33.054 --> 01:35.251
And what's he still doing here?

01:36.127 --> 01:37.743
If it weren't for Niels,

01:37.768 --> 01:39.649
we wouldn't have found
that doctor down the coast

01:39.674 --> 01:40.712
and their labs.

01:40.737 --> 01:42.403
Yeah, all right.

01:42.428 --> 01:45.346
Thank you very much!

01:45.766 --> 01:48.766
We don't need him hanging
around now creeping people out.

01:48.847 --> 01:50.837
He's like the grim reaper.

01:50.862 --> 01:52.876
That's all part of the plan.

01:52.901 --> 01:56.076
Niels' special talent's the
thing we've been looking for.

01:56.422 --> 01:59.547
That reaper's gonna
help us find more immunes

01:59.572 --> 02:01.739
just by breathing on them.

02:09.631 --> 02:13.049
Rachel: My lab is low
on just about everything.

02:13.074 --> 02:16.274
Once I have depleted the
cell cultures on hand,

02:16.299 --> 02:19.072
we won't be able to manufacture
the vaccine on the ship.

02:19.441 --> 02:20.837
- [Door closes]
- Anything on that sub?

02:20.862 --> 02:23.650
No. For all we know, they're
halfway back to England by now.

02:24.279 --> 02:26.040
Keep widening the search area.

02:26.065 --> 02:28.040
Farthest on circle from point last seen...

02:28.065 --> 02:29.398
24-hour range.

02:29.423 --> 02:31.845
Sir, if I may, to continue the search,

02:31.869 --> 02:33.289
we're gonna burn through all of our fuel.

02:33.315 --> 02:35.681
We'll top it off in Norfolk or Mayport.

02:35.705 --> 02:38.118
There's a naval weapons
station in Charleston.

02:38.143 --> 02:41.509
Wait... excuse me for
interrupting, but it seems to me

02:41.533 --> 02:44.031
that the longer we seek out this submarine,

02:44.057 --> 02:45.640
the further it takes us off our mission.

02:45.665 --> 02:47.485
We need to rebuild the labs

02:47.510 --> 02:49.266
or find one with enough
stock of cell culture.

02:49.291 --> 02:52.042
Where would you suggest we go?

02:53.886 --> 02:55.051
Which lab?

02:55.076 --> 02:58.261
Go on. Pick one.

02:59.647 --> 03:02.743
Phoenix... Destroyed, no survivors.

03:02.768 --> 03:05.152
Salt lake... Destroyed, no survivors.

03:05.177 --> 03:07.556
Madison, Topeka... gone.

03:07.580 --> 03:08.796
Baltimore.

03:08.821 --> 03:11.305
Baltimore, which I so cleverly added

03:11.330 --> 03:13.080
to the secret lab network... Gone.

03:13.113 --> 03:14.001
Florida.

03:14.026 --> 03:15.392
Everything we worked for!

03:15.416 --> 03:17.166
Captain, do you not
think I'm aware of this?

03:17.537 --> 03:20.777
I have spent the last 20
hours trying to figure out

03:20.802 --> 03:23.019
why this could have happened,
how this could have happened.

03:23.044 --> 03:27.282
But we need to stay on course

03:27.307 --> 03:31.352
or millions more are going to die.

03:34.170 --> 03:36.371
That sub is the mission now.

